President Trump addressed a group of senior citizens in Fort Myers, Florida, reaffirming his commitment to protecting and supporting America's seniors. He acknowledged the challenges that seniors have faced during the COVID-19 pandemic and promised to fight for their well-being. He emphasized his administration's efforts to provide care, support, and respect for senior citizens, including the development of therapeutics and vaccines. He also criticized the healthcare proposals of the Democratic Party, arguing that they would harm seniors and lead to rationed care and higher taxes. The President highlighted his administration's achievements in lowering prescription drug costs and expanding access to healthcare for seniors. He concluded by expressing optimism for the future and promising to protect Medicare and Social Security.